The DMDC equation implies that dark matter is a dynamic entity that evolves over time. This dynamic nature can affect the formation and evolution of galaxies.
*Alternative to Particle-Based Models*
The DMDC equation offers an alternative to particle-based models of dark matter. This alternative perspective can provide new insights into the nature of dark matter and its role in the universe.
